  "prompt": "How can you add money to a debit card from another card?",
  "response": "Adding money to a debit card from another card can be done through several methods, depending on the banks, card networks, and services available. Here are some common ways to transfer funds:\n\n### **1. Online or Mobile Banking Transfer**\n   - Log in to your bank\u2019s online or mobile app.\n   - Navigate to the \u201cTransfer\u201d or \u201cMove Money\u201d section.\n   - Select the debit card you want to fund as the destination account.\n   - Choose the other card (credit or debit) as the source account.\n   - Enter the amount and confirm the transfer.\n\n   **Note:** Some banks may charge fees for transfers between external cards.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Peer-to-Peer (P2P) Payment Apps**\n   - Use apps like **Venmo**, **Cash App**, **PayPal**, or **Zelle**.\n   - Link both cards to the app.\n   - Transfer funds from one card to your app balance.\n   - Withdraw the funds to your debit card.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Over-the-Counter Deposit**\n   - Visit a branch of the bank that issued your debit card.\n   - Provide the account details or card number.\n   - Use the other card to deposit funds into your debit card account.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Direct Bank Transfer**\n   - Use the routing and account number associated with your debit card.\n   - Initiate a transfer from the other card\u2019s linked bank account.\n\n---\n\n### **5. ATM Transfer**\n   - Some ATMs allow transfers between linked accounts or cards.\n   - Insert the source card and follow the prompts to transfer funds to your debit card.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Cash Advance (Credit Card to Debit Card)**\n   - If the source card is a credit card, you can perform a **cash advance** (though this usually incurs fees and higher interest rates).\n   - Deposit the cash into your bank account linked to the debit card.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Considerations**\n   - **Fees:** Transfers between cards or accounts may incur fees.\n   - **Limits:** Check daily transfer or funding limits.\n   - **Processing Time:** Some methods may take several business days.\n\nAlways confirm with your bank or card issuer for specific instructions and restrictions.",
